The paper deals with graph properties and their algorithmic complexity, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of the term "extendible properties" and the reference to the Poljak-Turzik bound suggest that the paper could be related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The mention of fixed-parameter tractability (FPT) and the use of certain classes of graphs also suggest that the paper could be related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also deals with graph theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG), as it mentions the problem of finding a subgraph satisfying a given property. Overall, cs.DM and cs.CC seem to be the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.GT, and cs.CG.
